The L, I had managed; but, for my right hand, I could
not imagine another word that began with U, except
uncle; and
that!
ah I could not think of immortalizing
my uncle in my poetry. He was too hateful to me. So,
I gave up the acrostick; and! loved on, like the
sunflower
,
through shadow and shine, tillas it hath always
happened to them, that I have loved,she got
miserably
