nobody?
I cried.
Nobody!
echoed the wall.
I shut my eyes. I lay without breath or motion. Yes,
yes. The truth had come at last. It was plain. I was
a dead man. I was in the charnel house. Or, had I
been buried alive? These were not chains;they were
