show a piece of cambrick muslin, wet it, the
agreeable
creatures! with their own spittle, and draw it
tightly over the tip end of the fore finger of the left hand;
thereby making it appear at least one hundred per cent.
better, than it really is;---or live by damaging goods,
when the demand for
damaged goods
---and goods that
have been shipwrecked---is at the highest; (for, such
economy
will rage, like madness, at times, among the
women
;
whose maxim is, always to buy what is cheap,
whether
they want it or not; forgetful of the truth, that
nothing
is
